detailedReviews.author: Doug Fischer
detailedReviews.text: I was out and about and decided to stop here for something quick, glad I did. Got some pizza, cutlets, and soup. All 3 things were done well, the plain slice being a good indicator that the rest of their pizza is probably good. All for cheap too.

detailedReviews.author: Anthony Girratano
detailedReviews.text: This place easily has the best pizza in Roxbury hands down. Unlike many pizza places Anthony Francos also has a great assortment of Italian style dinners which each have flavors beyond what most everyday pizza places usually serve putting some other places in the area to shame. I recommend a chicken franchise pizza cooked well done with a large antipasto to compliment it. Also be patient!! Because of how amazing they are they are usually super busy, trust me when I tell you it's worth the wait!

detailedReviews.author: Dana Leavy
detailedReviews.text: Anthony Francos never disappoints. My family and I go weekly for our usual pizza nights, but the last few times we've been ordering dinners. The chicken saltimbocca I last ordered was incredible. The sauce was delicious and the chicken was tender. I'm very particular with my chicken. I had mine over angel hair. My husband has always been a big fan of their vodka sauce (he usually gets it over a chicken cutlet sandwich) but this time he order their chicken penne vodka dinner. That was amazing and is his new go-to. These portions were so large we actually had full dinners for the next night. We also love their mozzarella sticks, garlic knots, and calamari. If you asked the kids, Anthony Francos has the best chicken fingers in the world.  We can't wait to head back tonight!

detailedReviews.author: Pat Gerges
detailedReviews.text: Since I've gotten old and unable to cook for friends, we have placed several large orders with Anthony Franco's.  We have been impressed with the quality, presentation, and taste of everything we have ordered.  The garlic knots, chicken Parm, penne Alla vodka, and stuffed shells are our favorites, but we were not dissatisfied with any of the dishes we received.  The potato skins pizza is our favorite pie.  Kudos for being timely, fresh, delicious, and reliable.

detailedReviews.author: Raffaele Maffei
detailedReviews.text:
I started writing this big, long and detailed review/ description of this place,  and about 3 paragraphs in,  I decided 1) no one has the time to read a story like that but 2) and really more importantly, this restaurant, this specific location in particular,  is LEGIT.

From the 1st time I tried it,  to each and every time since,  quality,  delicious food made with top shelf ingredients.  I'll sum it up by saying this,  and you other foodies out there will know right away what I mean.

How many times do you get chicken from a pizza place,  and it's the rubbery chicken flap they get from a restaurant depot in bulk to save money?? More often that not right? Then,  once in a while,  you get a pizzeria where you unexpectedly bite into a chicken dish,  and it's a nice,  thick,  juicy piece of actual chicken, and you're literally like "whoa, that's delicious" yeah,  that's this place,  but with everything
